# Edge case: deep function-of-function chain in a rate law
# Tests:  BNG2 promotes any parameter whose expression references
#         another *expression-typed* parameter into a Function in the
#         emitted XML (constants stay as ListOfParameters; expressions
#         become entries in ListOfFunctions).  A 5-level chain forces
#         RM's function-evaluator to recursively resolve a -> a4 -> a3
#         -> a5 -> rate per propensity recompute.  ft_nested_functions
#         exercises a 3-level chain (frac_P -> modulator -> phos_rate);
#         this stretches the chain to 5 deep AND declares the
#         dependencies in non-topological order so the loader cannot
#         resolve in declaration order.
# Edge:   intermediate "parameters" a3,a4,a5 all evaluate to 1 (a1=a2=1),
#         so rate = base = 0.01.  A miswired chain would silently zero
#         out the propensity (the failure mode RM falls back to when
#         resolve_value throws).  The compute_observables fast-path
#         must also keep the function values fresh.
# Tier:   base

begin model
begin parameters
    # Declared in non-topological order so the second-pass forward-
    # ref resolver actually has to do work.
    rate    base * a5
    a3      a2 * a4
    a4      a1 * a2
    a5      a3 * a2
    a1      1.0
    a2      1.0
    base    0.01
    k_death 0.0
end parameters

begin molecule types
    Src()
    A()
    Trash()
end molecule types

begin seed species
    Src()      1
    A()        0
    $Trash()   0
end seed species

begin observables
    Molecules  A_total  A()
end observables

begin reaction rules
    Src() -> Src() + A()  rate
    A()   -> Trash()       k_death
end reaction rules
end model

begin actions
simulate({method=>"nf",t_end=>40,n_steps=>80})
end actions
